 TASK 1 - Create a Digital Literacy Awareness Infographic 

In this assignment, I created a one-page infographic on Canva to create awareness of digital literacy. The graphic simply describes the meaning of digital literacy in easy to understand, school-friendly language and why it is important to us, as students. I divided it into four parts: (1) the definition of digital literacy, (2) the list of necessary digital tools: GitHub, Canva etc., (3) safe internet practices: using strong passwords, two-factor authorization, avoiding suspicious links, etc.
When assembling the design, the best part involved was the arrangement of the information in a manner that is not too congested. The most difficult part was the choice of a layout which contains all the major points on one page and can still be read. I have found out that infographics are the most appealing when they are short bullet points, icons are regular and color palette is neat. The given task allowed me to understand that digital literacy means not only the knowledge of how to operate tech but also its responsible, safe, and professional use.

